A business has received the following class B address: 172.16.0.0
This primary network must be subdivided into 430 equal-sized subnetworks.

1 - How many bits must be borrowed from the HostID section to create 430 subnetworks?

	9 bits



2 - How many bits remain in the HostID section for each subnetwork?

	7 bits



3 - How many hosts does each subnetwork have?

	125 (2^7 - 3)



4 - What is the subnetwork mask in CIDR and binary representation ?

	dec : 255.255.255.128 /25
	bin : 1111 1111.1111 111.1111 1111.1000 0000
